  <prompt>
    Build the canonical `<SendEmailPage />` wrapper at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/wrappers/SendEmailPage.tsx`. Locks `mount='page'`. Supports all 5 modes — the Code Page (Wave 2) drives `mode` from URL parameters.

    Props (FR-04):
    - `mode: EmailComposerMode` — driven by URL `?mode=compose|view|reply|forward|draft`
    - `communicationId?: string` — required when `mode ∈ {view, reply, forward, draft}`; the `sprk_communication` record to load
    - `initialTo?: IRecipient[] | string` — only used in `compose` mode
    - `initialCc?: IRecipient[] | string`
    - `initialSubject?: string`
    - `initialBody?: string`
    - `initialBodyFormat?: 'html' | 'plaintext'`
    - `associations?: IComposerAssociation[]` — URL `?associatedTo=` parses into this
    - `attachmentSources?: IComposerAttachmentSource[]` — defaults to `[{ kind: 'local' }, { kind: 'spe' }, { kind: 'related' }]` for full Code Page experience
    - `authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch`
    - `onSent?: (communicationId: string) => void`
    - `onClose?: () => void` — Code Page may navigate back via Xrm.Navigation; passed through

    Implementation responsibilities:
    - Validate prop combos: `view`/`reply`/`forward`/`draft` require `communicationId` — throw a helpful error if missing
    - Mode-specific load: for `view`/`reply`/`forward`/`draft`, load the existing record via Xrm.WebApi.retrieveRecord('sprk_communication', communicationId) and pass into engine as initial state. The actual mode-specific pre-fill logic (e.g., reply prefix, forward attachment carry) is in tasks 024-027 (mode files); this wrapper just passes the loaded record through to the engine
    - For `compose` mode: pass initialX props through directly
    - Render `<EmailComposer mount='page' mode={mode} ref={composerRef} ... />` — engine + ComposerActionBar handle the bottom-right action chrome for `page` mount

    Page-level header (NFR-03): wrapper renders a Fluent v9 page header above the engine showing entity context (e.g., "New Email" / "Re: <subject>" / "Draft: <subject>" / "Email from <sender>" based on mode + state). Header is part of `page` mount chrome; engine reserves space for it.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React developer; familiar with mode-dispatch + URL-driven state patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SendEmailPage.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. Locks `mount='page'`. All 5 modes supported. Prop validation enforces `communicationId` requirement for non-compose modes. Page-level header renders mode-appropriate title. Wave 2 Code Page (task 033) consumes this.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-04 + FR-18: the Code Page is the full-form-replacement surface. It opens with `?mode=compose|view|reply|forward|draft&id={guid}&to=&cc=&subject=&body=&associatedTo=`. The wrapper's job is to take these URL-derived props and render the engine correctly.

      Mode load: for `view`/`reply`/`forward`/`draft`, the wrapper fetches the existing `sprk_communication` record. Engine receives the record (via `initialX` props plus a `sourceRecord` prop for mode-specific logic — tasks 024-027 fill in the mode-specific pre-fill behavior).

      Per NFR-03 page mount visual variant: page-level header + full-width form chrome + bottom-right prominent action bar. Header rendered by wrapper; engine renders the rest.
    </background>
