  <steps>
    <step order="1">Update `EmailComposer.types.ts` to add `IComposerSourceRecord` shape — minimum: `{ communicationId: string; subject: string; body: string; bodyFormat: 'html'|'plaintext'; from: IRecipient; to: IRecipient[]; cc: IRecipient[]; attachments: IAttachment[]; associations: IComposerAssociation[]; internetMessageId?: string; threadId?: string; statusCode?: 'Draft'|'Sent' }`. Add `sourceRecord?: IComposerSourceRecord` to `IEmailComposerProps`.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `SendEmailPage.tsx`:
      - Props per prompt
      - Prop validation: if `mode !== 'compose' &amp;&amp; !communicationId`, throw `new Error('SendEmailPage requires communicationId for mode='+mode)`
      - `useEffect`-driven load: when `mode !== 'compose'`, fetch the record via `Xrm.WebApi.retrieveRecord('sprk_communication', communicationId)` (or BFF fallback) and set local state `sourceRecord`
      - Compute page-header title based on mode + sourceRecord (e.g., `compose` → "New Email"; `view` → `Email: ${sourceRecord.subject}`; `reply` → `Re: ${sourceRecord.subject}`; etc.)
      - Render: `&lt;Title2&gt;{headerTitle}&lt;/Title2&gt;` then `&lt;EmailComposer mount='page' mode={mode} sourceRecord={sourceRecord} ...props /&gt;`</step>
    <step order="3">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` — export `SendEmailPage`, `ISendEmailPageProps`, `IComposerSourceRecord`.</step>
    <step order="4">Smoke test in dev: all 5 mode URLs render correctly (compose with no id; view/reply/forward/draft each fetches sourceRecord).</step>
    <step order="5">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="5.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check (ADR-021, ADR-024, ADR-026, ADR-028, ADR-033).</step>
    <step order="6">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 023 ✅.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

